6:
Will you assist me in keeping Subaru
safe?
8: I have a plan, but I can't do it alone—
12:
Whoa, slow down. Mind explaining
what's going on first?
19: My apologies, I got ahead of myself.
21:
I'd like your help installing security
measures across the mansion.
25:
I assume this is because of what
happened before. Are you worried
it'll happen again?
28: Yes. Better to be safe than sorry.
30:
I'm not that familiar with Palpebra,
which is why I'd like to ask for your
help.
35:
In that case, we would be happy to
lend our aid.
42:
First of all, I'd like to set up a barrier
around the mansion that will detect
intruders.
46:
Hmm, the Academy should be able
to do that—though it might be
expensive.
49:
Next, I'd like to install security
devices inside individual rooms and
by windows. Some sort of shock trap
would be preferable.
52:
We should also have offensive
mechanisms in the hallways and
walls for optimum protection—
58:
Okay, hold it right there! You're
gonna turn the place into a fort with
those kind of measures!
63:
But this is the bare minimum for a
satisfactory level of security.
67:
Y-your standards are quite high.
Surely the mansion doesn't require
that much in terms of defenses—
70:
Yesterday, we had thieves break in. I
don't think a simple barrier is
enough.
75:
You had what now?! D-did anybody
get hurt?
79:
Only the thieves. I rounded them all
up and delivered them to the Guild. I
even received a thank-you letter for
it.
83:
Surely just a barrier is fine then, if
you're that strong...
88:
It's not enough! We need far more to
keep Subaru safe!
90:
I want to protect him from any and
all danger. I can't stand the thought
of a single hair on his head being
harmed. That's how I feel about this!
95:
I do understand where you're
coming from, but...
100:
Trust me, we do want to help.
There's just a big problem with this...
108:
I see... With the monetary rewards
being so low, even erecting just the
barrier will be difficult.
111:
Not much you can do about that...
This is about average for work
around these parts.
116:
What a shame. I would have liked to
be able to remodel the mansion
and add room for traps and
magical devices...
120: Y-you were willing to do all that?!
124:
Yes, I want to do all I can to ensure
that Subaru can live a pleasant life.
129:
You are quite passionate when it
comes to Subaru...
133:
Hmm... Why don't we see how much
we can realistically get done then?
135:
Maybe there's some other way to
get the money, but it may take
some time—
139:
No. Before we consider other
options, there's something I'd like to
check first.
146:
You're looking for high-paying jobs
that haven't been officially listed yet?
156:
Give me one moment. The one that
comes to mind is...
160:
Here we go—a demolition job for an
old building! Been waiting for a
construction team to swing by—
165:
Demolition? I can do that. I'll accept
this job.
175:
Whoa, wait, are you seriously
considering letting Rem have it?
179:
Er, I'm more confused. You sure just
the three of you can demolish a
whole building?
184:
I already signed the contract. Now
where's the building?
187:
Rest assured, I'll get the job done. I
can be fanatical as a demon when
it comes to doing something for
Subaru's sake—more than anyone
else.
193:
Yep, here it is. No monsters... Just a
regular old building.
197:
You know, it's not too late to go back
to the Guild and tell them we can't
do it—
203:
As you can see, the structure is
already weak. I can destroy all of it
just fine.
205:
Please wait right there. I'll be done
soon.
212:
I had trouble with a few parts, but I
think this counts as demolished, yes?
216:
That was AMAZING. She was like a
wrecking ball!
220:
H-her strength certainly is a sight to
behold. Is this what they call... the
power of love?
224:
All that's left is to report our success
to the Guild and have someone else
remove the debris.
231:
With all the other jobs we got done,
we finally have enough money.
235:
I don't know how I can possibly
thank you... But I really appreciate it!
242:
I'm not sure we contributed
anything whatsoever...
246:
You accompanied me throughout
everything on such short notice.
Your emotional support was crucial.
251:
Now that we've spent some time
together, I think I've learned a thing
or two about you.
254:
Especially how, when it comes to
Subaru, you don't hold back.
258:
That's right! I want to do whatever I
can for Subaru.
261:
In exchange for all your help today,
I'll help you whenever you need it.
263:
So the next time you go on an
adventure, don't hesitate to call on
me.
267:
Sounds good to me. It'll be a relief to
have someone as strong as you on
our side.
